KeyList module¶

KeyList([separator])

Stores list of keys for future access.

This file contains the KeyList class. This class stores keys for future access. Keys are stored in dictionary. Dictionary key is the prefix codename for each key. Dictionary value is the collection of keys containing that prefix.

class KeyList.KeyList(separator=' ')[source]

Bases: object

Stores list of keys for future access. Keys are generated as prefix + separator + tag.

Variables

  • prefixes – dictionary from prefix codename to prefix

  • separator – string separating prefix and tag

  • keys – dictionary from prefix codename to all keys stored under that prefix codename
